Market Analysis and Insights

Environment, Health and Safety (EHS) Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the environment, health and safety (EHS) market will exhibit a CAGR of 10.83% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Rising number of accidents at mining, oil and gas and chemical plants, supportive governmental regulations, policies and guidelines and increased application of EHS software by the various end user verticals such as energy and utilities, chemicals and materials, healthcare, construction and engineering, chemicals and material, food and beverage, government and defense and others are the major factors attributable to the growth of environment, health and safety (EHS) market. This signifies that the market value would climb up to USD 12.74 billion by the year 2028.

EHS, which stands for environment, health and safety, is responsible for dealing with protecting the environment and maintaining health and safety at occupation. EHS is responsible for looking after the undue and uncertain cause that might affect or might affect the environment and put the safety of workers at risk.

Induced focus on undertaking corporate social responsibilities and to bring transformation in business continuity is generating lucrative growth opportunities for the EHS market. Upsurge in the awareness regarding EHS software will further induce growth in the EHS market value. Rising expenditure on the deployment of EHS software for small and medium scale enterprises is another factor fostering the growth of this market.

However, dearth of skilled professionals or trained personnel will pose a major challenge to the growth of Environment, health and safety (EHS) market. High costs associated with the EHS software couple with competitive pressure of pricing will further create hurdles for the market growth rate.

